The over 60 national executives were sworn-in by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng and his deputy, Raymond Zondo, at the Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria, South Africa. The reduced executive also comprised of young people with a fifty-fifty gender representation. New faces include Deputy Finance Minister David Masondo, who said his key priority will be to work to attract investment and stimulate job creation.

--SABC--